      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>If your body does not produce insulin the right way then the problem is diabetes. Every single year, this disease is going to affect millions of people. Diabetes can cause different skin problems and the answer is because it will affect the body too. People will usually see a doctor because they think that they have skin disorder and that is how they find out they are suffering from diabetes.</p>
<p>There are different things that you can do to protect your skin, if you do have diabetes. There are some tips that can be used to <a href="http://www.lotionsecret.com/skin-care-lotion">take care of your skin</a> if you have diabetes.</p>
<p>You have to see your doctor on a regular basis and when you have diabetes you need to use self-testing supplies daily to make sure that your sugar levels in the blood stream are under control. You can be sure to reduce the risk of developing skin problems and take control your illness.</p>
<p>It is also important to treat your skin carefully. Use very mild products that are made for dry skin and sensitive, you need it. Your skin will be extra sensitive and may always get dry or have acne breakouts. You need to avoid hard products like <a href="http://www.lotionsecret.com/bath-lotion">regular body soap</a> and treat cuts and bruises immediately. Very important for anyone to having a good skin care. It makes no difference if you have diabetes or not. Cleaning your skin with natural products and mild soap like shampoos and other hair care items that will not damage your scalp is very important too. Using <a href="http://www.lotionsecret.com/lotion-beauty">moisturizers and toners</a> that are going to help your skin can help keep it looking healthy and you will be happy no matter what other medical problems you might have. Your doctor will give you how to have the right skin care and give you more information on what you should do to stay healthy and safe if you deal with diabetes too.</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.diabetescarenow.com">Diabetes Care</a> site, where you can get information and resources about diabetes symptoms, gestational diabetes, and more.<br/><br/><a href="http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/vital-pieces-of-diabetes/">Vital Pieces Of Diabetes</a></p>


