to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center>
<p style="text-align:center;"><object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/ZHVkA15HmbM&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/ZHVkA15HmbM&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></embed></object></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZHVkA15HmbM">Sample Diabetes Meal Plan</a></p>
<p></center>
<p>Diabetes is a sickness that is composed of unnatural blood sugar levels.  Diabetes can come in the shape of either Type one or Type two.  Some of the complications of this sickness can be kidney failure, heart attack, or blindness.  Many diabetics suffer from being overweight, too.  It's a myth that only middle age and older people get diabetes.  Nowadays, more and more young folks are too due to unhealthy eating habits and absence of exercise. </p>
<p> How is diabetes treated? <br /> Medical treatments can come in the form of both oral medicines and insulin injections.  Additionally, a correct diet and regular exercise can be effective.  Any kind of exercise, whether it's walking, jogging, or working out can help, just as long as it is done at least a number of times week. </p>
<p> Aful reasonable healthy} diet may also be helpful for diabetics.  This is because areasonable healthy~ healthful} diet can make blood levels easier to control.  It could also aid in weight reduction.  The higher a person's blood level, the more capacity their body has to put on body fat.  For an adult, lowering blood levels can be really troublesome.  A sample Sample Diabetes Meal Plan will consist of sensible food that may reduce fat, bring blood glucose levels in order, and help an individual to become healthier overall. <br /> Where can you get a sample Sample Diabetes Meal Plan? </p>
<p> Sample meal plans are found on the internet.  Doctors can only give patience medication, but they cannot force a patient to eat better.  Thanks to Internet technology, you can simply find a sample plan that may assist you in losing weight and give you more energy. <br /> A special diet plan for those with diabetes consists of : 1,400 - 1,600 calories a day, 220 grams of good carbs, and masses of water.  You need to drink at least 2 glasses of water with each meal.  You need to eat three, healthful meals together with two snacks each single day. </p>
<p> to give you some ideas, here is a sample Sample Diabetes Meal Plan :<br /> Breakfast<br /> one chopped toast on wholeweat bread<br /> cup of cottage cheese<br /> cup of oatmeal<br /> cup of skim milk<br /> of a banana</p>
<p> This should equal out to about 360 calories and 52 grams of carbohydrates. <br /> Lunch</p>
<p> one cup of vegetable broth with five crackers<br /> one turkey sandwich on entire wheat bread that is composed of one oz. turkey, one ounce of low fat cheese, and a bit of mayo<br /> one apple</p>
<p> This should be around 530 calories and seventy five grams of carbs. </p>
<p> Dinner</p>
<p> 4 ounces of sauteed chicken breast<br /> 2/3 cup of cooked brown rice<br /> 1 tiny whole grain dinner roll<br /> cup of cooked carrots<br /> 1 small slice angel food cake<br /> Tossed salad with just 2 tablespoons of low-fat dressing</p>
<p> this should be around 635 calories and 65 grams of carbohydrates. </p>
<p> snacks</p>
<p> You can pick two small nibbles a day.  These are 60 calories each. </p>
<p> 3 cups of light popcorn<br /> A small fruit with one oz of string cheese<br /> 16 fat free tortilla chips<br /> cup of diet chocolate pudding</p>
<p> Stick with this sample Sample Diabetes Meal Plan each day, work out 4-6 times per week, drink lots of water, and check with your doctor regularly.  Always take your medicine exactly as your doctor tells you to, also.</p>
<p>Come visit us here for your three free Diabetic Diet Ebooks: <a href="http://diabeticdietzone.com/">Sample Diabetes Meal Plan</a> http://diabeticdietzone.com.</p>
