More Diabetes Care information:&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/pre-diabetic-foods-tricks-information/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Pre Diabetic Foods Tricks Information'&gt;Pre Diabetic Foods Tricks Information&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Pre Diabetic Foods Pre diabetic foods should consist of...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/find-pre-diabetes-recipes/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Find Pre Diabetes Recipes'&gt;Find Pre Diabetes Recipes&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Pre Diabetes Recipes The best pre diabetes recipes can...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/gestational-diabetes-diet-tips-and-information/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Gestational Diabetes Diet Tips and Information'&gt;Gestational Diabetes Diet Tips and Information&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Gestational Diabetes Diet Gestational diabetes is just as serious...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/go-with-diabetic-diet-plan-now/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Go With Diabetic Diet Plan Now'&gt;Go With Diabetic Diet Plan Now&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Perhaps one of the biggest problem of all that...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/pre-diabetes-diet-tips/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Pre Diabetes Diet Tips'&gt;Pre Diabetes Diet Tips&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Pre Diabetes Diet With pre diabetes you fundamentally have...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/diabetes-care/Diabetes_Care-Pre_Diabetic_Menus_Tricks_Information.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center>
<p style="text-align:center;"><object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/unDfjF7H69o&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/unDfjF7H69o&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></embed></object></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=unDfjF7H69o">Pre Diabetic Menus</a></p>
<p></center>
<p>Developing a pre diabetic menu can actually be extremely simple if you learn how to read nutrition labels and know what your ideal calorie intake should be.  With pre diabetes, you'll basically wish to start to watch what you eat and learn how to eat better.  You may want to watch your calorie intake, consume fewer fat grams, less sodium, less sugar and fewer carbohydrates. </p>
<p> You don't have to chop these completely out of your diet and you don't have to starve yourself by eating extremely low amounts of them.  Just learn the way to divide your intake per meal, so that you're still able to enjoy your meals, at sometime during the day or week, even though you might not be able to have it at every meal or even every day.  In other words, if you still have to have your Snickers candy bar, reward yourself once each week, just make sure to count it into your daily intake for that day. </p>
<p> seeking Help - You can seek help from a dietician or you find internet sites on the internet that may help you to outline your pre diabetic menus for the week.  Until you are able to do this on your own, if wouldn't be a bad idea if you find help in preparing your menu in the beginning stages of your diagnosis period.  Once you have became aware and informed and educated on the topic, then you'll be able to continue on your own without the help of anyone else. </p>
<p> Another excellent idea is to ask someone for help who has already been diagnosed as a diabetic.  Nine possibilities out of 10 then will have some great advice to give to you as they have just been there and still are at this point in their lives. <br /> Your physician is there for you and anytime that you change your diet you must inform your surgeon.  They can help guide you in the right direction because they will be able to monitor your progress or relapse based upon what you are doing at the present time. </p>
<p> Eating healthier - Eating fitter is the entire point is improving your diet once you have been determined to be pre diabetic.  Think about how you usually would eat and then adjust in an appropriate way.  In the past, did you eat a lot of sweets?  If yes, then cut them down in your new diet plan.  This is only one of the ways that you can learn how to develop your own pre diabetic menu. </p>
<p> Make sure to include protein, plants, fiber, fruits and vitamins into your new diet.  Find out what proper proportion sizes are and follow them.  As an example, does one oz of protein equal one serving?  Things like this, you should learn.  Once you learn these key factors and learn how to read nutrition labels and discover what your proper daily calorie intake should be, you may start to have a better understanding of developing a proper pre diabetic menu that you will be able to follow and be in a position to live by.</p>
