escription>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center>
<p style="text-align:center;"><object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/mLJGV4hwMkg&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/mLJGV4hwMkg&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></embed></object></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mLJGV4hwMkg">Gestational Diabetes Symptoms</a></p>
<p></center>
<p>Diabetes symptoms, if it is gestational diabetes symptoms or evidence of other types of diabetes, are dissimilar and can change from individual to individual.  Please keep this under consideration as you read thru this article, as this is only to serve as a suggestion and can't forecast the symptoms that each individual person may experience. </p>
<p> indications of diabetes come in different forms and degrees.  Even though you may not be experiencing any obvious symptoms doesn't mean that you are not a diabetic.  Sometimes it takes weeks or even months for symptoms to become common to where you'll see them.  With a pregnancy, doctors will usually order a glucose tolerance test at a certain stage in the pregnancy and this can help to determine whether you are experiencing gestational diabetes or not ; however, although the original test may come back negative does not mean that you cannot develop gestational diabetes at a later stage of the pregnancy.  Often, gestational diabetes shows no symptoms and is found thru the glucose toleration test.  If symptoms are noticeable, they're mild. </p>
<p> Symptoms - common manifestations and signs of diabetes, whether gestational or not, are : steady thirst, excessive pissing, fatigue, blurred vision, continued infections of the bladder, vagina and skin, blurred vision, and weight reduction ( even though you've got an increased appetite ).  These are just a few of the basic symptoms and signs of diabetes as each person may experience different signs and symptoms. <br /> weight reduction happens when the body doesn't receive sugar ( energy ) thru consumption ( sometimes resulting in hyperglycemia ) and then the body begins to burn stored sugar ( fat ) for energy.  When this happens, your blood sugar levels are sometimes high and in some cases, extremely high and desires attention as fast as possible before the onset on ketoacidosis and possible diabetic coma. </p>
<p> Gestational Diabetes &amp; Type 2 Diabetes - Gestational diabetes is caused due to the hormones developed during the pregnancy and is like Type two diabetes in the body is still manufacturing insulin even though it's not enough to manipulate blood glucose levels.  Occasionally you can control gestational diabetes through watching your diet alone ; however some may have to take medicine and possibly even insulin through the pregnancy. </p>
<p> there is some research that shows that gestational diabetes and Type two diabetes is related ; however just because you develop gestational diabetes during pregnancy does not mean that you will develop Type two diabetes later in life.  To help curve the chance of this, maintain a health{ful sensible healthy} diet and a healthy weight as you can help to reduce your chance of developing Type two diabetes later on down the road. </p>
<p> If in Doubt.If you think that you are experiencing symptoms of gestational diabetes, inform your surgeon immediately.  Like mentioned earlier, even though the 1st test may come back negative, doesn't mean that you haven't developed gestational diabetes since it was conducted.  Consultants often wait to conduct the glucose tolerance test about 28 weeks of pregnancy.  If you are feeling at any point during your pregnancy like you are experiencing evidence of diabetes, your surgeon may wish to either conduct an early test or a later test.  Don't be afraid to let your physician know what is happening with you, as it is your body and only you know how you are feeling. </p>
<p> .</p>
