e="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/diabetes-care/Diabetes_Care-Gestational_Diabetes_Meal_Plan_Tricks_Information.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center>
<p style="text-align:center;"><object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/65nzkCv14XI&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/65nzkCv14XI&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></embed></object></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=65nzkCv14XI">Gestational Diabetes Meal Plan</a></p>
<p></center>
<p>There are three types of diabetes : Type I, Type II, and Gestational diabetes.  Gestational diabetes can develop in a pregnant woman.  If not treated properly, it may result in the baby being born atypically enormous.  Older girls and chunky ladies are especially in peril to develop Gestational diabetes, although each pregnant woman should be checked for it.  Typically, it develops between 24 and twenty-eight weeks of pregnancy.  If it is in time, Gestational diabetes can be handled. </p>
<p> roughly 4% of all pregnant women develop this kind of diabetes when pregnant.  It is rather like Type II diabetes, in that insulin injections, oral medication, diet, and exercise can aid in treatment.  Some of the factors that are believed to cause an increase for the chance include : genetic, obesity, too much amniotic fluid, past history of giving birth to a large infant, or having had a stillborn child. </p>
<p> if you are worried that you, or that somebody you know, could have Gestational diabetes, you want to establish a good, smart Gestational Diabetes meal plan.  Remember , however , that there's no'one' diet for each diabetic.  Thankfully , there are some tenets you can go by in ensuring that you eat correctly. </p>
<p> Where are you able to find ideas for a Gestational diabetes meal plan? </p>
<p> the internet is full of great info about every kind of diabetes.  There are great resources online that will help you get through every aspect of your Gestational diabetes.  To get you moving, these are some general rules for a diet plan :</p>
<p> concepts for Breakfast<br /> unprocessed wheat bread<br /> Dry cereal with skim milk<br /> Starchy vegetables<br /> Bagel with one teaspoon of jam</p>
<p> concepts for Lunch</p>
<p> 2 pieces of whole wheat bread for a sandwich with :<br /> two oz. of beef with protein, for example lean roast beef or tuna<br /> one fat like a tablespoon of mayo or salad dressing<br /> 1 plant, for example some lettuce or tomato<br /> 1 cup of milk or nonfat yogurt<br /> 1 fruit, such as strawberries or grapes<br /> 1'free' food or drink, for example un-sugared soft drink</p>
<p> ideas for Dinner</p>
<p> 3 oz protein or beef, for example salmon or grilled chicken<br /> a few carbohydrate choices such as :<br /> massive baked potato<br /> Cup of pasta<br /> 1 cup of melon cubes, fresh apricots, or other fruit<br /> Nonfat, sugar free yogurt<br /> For vegetables : two cups of tossed salad or 1 cup of steamed asparagus<br /> two fats, like lo-fat salad dressing or margarine</p>
<p> you need to also eat a small break between each meal.  Some choices include :</p>
<p> one slice entire wheat bread<br /> small bowl of sixteen, fat free tortilla chips<br /> six - 8 whole grain crackers<br /> Fat free pudding<br /> Cup of fruit</p>
<p> Tips</p>
<p> Your calorie intake for the day should consist of : roughly 245-250 grams of carbohydrate, 120-125 grams of protein, and 70 grams of fat. </p>
<p> Your eating patterns are very important, since you wish to make sure that you and your baby both are getting the right sort of nourishment.  It is essential that you keep your blood glucose levels underground.  You may ask your doctor for a personalised Gestational diabetes meal plan.  Make sure you stick with a good plan, drink masses of water, and talk with your doctor if you experience any Problems.</p>
<p>Come visit us here for your three free Diabetic Diet Ebooks: <a href="http://diabeticdietzone.com/">Gestational Diabetes Meal Plan</a> http://diabeticdietzone.com.</p>
