      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center>
<p style="text-align:center;"><object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/cIXzpYfKA9I&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/cIXzpYfKA9I&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></embed></object></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cIXzpYfKA9I">Gestational Diabetes Diet</a></p>
<p></center>
<p>Gestational diabetes is just as serious as other kinds of diabetes, although you may only be'diabetic' for a short period of time ; although with gestational diabetes, you aren't only worried about the condition of yourself but also the healthiness of your unborn kid.  So, in actuality, gestational diabetes can be even more heavy than other forms. </p>
<p> You should definitely take your diet seriously when it comes to gestational diabetes.  It may take some getting used to but bear in mind that it's just for a short period of time.  When you have been diagnosed as having gestational diabetes, your consultant will help to command you on ways to better care for yourself and for your unborn kid.  Sometimes just watching your diet can help , other times, you will have to enroll the help of medication or even insulin during your pregnancy. </p>
<p> Ay healthy~ sensible} diet is extremely critical after the diagnosis of gestational diabetes just as it was prior to the diagnosis.  You will need to make sure to cut out as much sugar out of your diet as possible, and to also consume lots of proteins and vitamins.  As a gestational diabetic, you'll essentially have the same symptoms as a Type 2 diabetic due to the hormones that are produced in the pregnancy.  Your body is still manufacturing insulin ; {however|although} it might not be adequate and a large amount of time by following a diabetic diet you will be in a position to help your body out and possibly even overcome the diabetic symptoms.  In reality, you will want to follow a diabetic menu for a Type 2 diabetic. </p>
<p> this suggests that your diet should be low in carbohydrates, low in sugar, low in sodium and high in protein and vitamins.  It is recommended that you consume vegetables and fruit although fruits have natural sugars ; {however|although} there are only certain fruits that you're going to wish to consume as some are extremely high and can put astrain strain~ stress} on your body. </p>
<p> seek help - Ask your surgeon, if they have not already, to suggest a dietician for you to check with, to help explain the different aspects of a diabetic diet and what you must and shouldn't do.  There are books available which will help as well as doing research on the web.  You'll definitely need to find out how to read a nourishment label and to even buy a book that gives you the nutrition guiding principles on foods that generally don't come with a label, like garden foods, fruits and so on .  This could prove to come in awfully handy in your education and appreciation of the gestational diabetes diet. </p>
<p> the proper diet is really easy to learn if you keep an unprejudiced mind and pay close attention to details.  In the long run, not only will you be better off by following gestational diabetes diet guiding principles but your unborn kid will be better off also.  Diabetes, irrespective of what type, is a serious condition and will be regarded as such.</p>
