betes_Recipes.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center>
<p style="text-align:center;"><object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/EN4JqVDR2CY&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/EN4JqVDR2CY&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></embed></object></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EN4JqVDR2CY">Free Diabetes Recipes</a></p>
<p></center>
<p>If you have lately conducted an internet search for free diabetes recipes, you doubtless discovered a wide variety of healthy, delicious meals and nibbles.  There are numerous sites that offer recipes for folk with Type I, Type II, and Gestational diabetes.  As a diabetic, you can still eat superb tasting foods.  You aren't restricted to just eating tasteless foods, as you can surmise from the large number of free diabetes recipes online . </p>
<p> If you like fish, chicken, potatoes, pudding, etc, you'll be glad to know that there are lots of recipes with these foods that are healthy for diabetics.  In fact, if you eat well balanced meals everyday and exercise frequently you'll be controlling your blood sugar level and so shed the pounds.  Overall, you will be improving and enhancing your general health! <br /> keep in mind when searching for free diabetes recipes that many of the results will be the same type of recipes found elsewhere.  To make sure that you actually are incorporating healthy food in your diet plan, you want to know what sort of content is usually found in diabetes recipes.  What protein, fats, sodium, carbohydrates, vitamins, minerals, etc, should you look for in a good meal? </p>
<p> Some free diabetes recipes will include detailed info regarding the servings,eg the number of calories, carbohydrate %, and so on.  It may seem like a large amount of work to prepare a healthy, diabetic health plan, but it is vital to your health.  You can also request assistance in making your plan.  Some nutritionists and gurus are available via the Net that will help you.  There are possibly some in your locale, as well . </p>
<p> So, what are some of the best, free diabetes recipes? </p>
<p> Well, to get you started, these are some really healthy foods that you'll find in the recipes. <br /> Breakfast foods<br /> Oatmeal<br /> egg whites<br /> whole wheat bread<br /> Anything that is high in fiber and digests easily</p>
<p> Lunch foods</p>
<p> French beans, aka kidney beans. <br /> Soya bean<br /> Tuna<br /> Salmon<br /> Cottage cheese</p>
<p> Dinner foods</p>
<p> Turkey<br /> griddled chicken<br /> Baked fish<br /> Chicken salad</p>
<p> Tips for free <a href="http://www.diabetescarenow.com/delicious-diabetic-recipes"  rel='nofollow' >diabetic recipes</a></p>
<p> make sure that your typical diet comprises of 15-18% proteins. <br /> snack on fruits like apples, apricots, and pomegranate. <br /> Try adding some spice to your meals with cinnamon or garlic.  They can lower blood sugar levels a great deal. <br /> Eat whole grains instead of packaged foods as frequently as you can.  Gains are just about the base of the diabetic food pyramid, which suggests they are extremely important for you to eat. <br /> the perfect diet for a diabetic consists of 50% calories from carbohydrates, 30 percent from fat, and 20% from protein. <br /> Eat a tiny snack in between each meal.  Eat at regular intervals during the day. </p>
<p> These are a few of the most important things you need to take into consideration when looking online for free diabetes recipes.  Ensure you follow correct guidelines and eat only food that is good for you.  It is OK to snack sometimes, but make sure you snack on food that is in low cal and fat free.</p>
