      <description>Diabetes Menu

Diabetes is a disorder where the body doesn't produce enough insulin to cover the consumption of food a person intakes, causing the blood sugar levels to rise.  Plenty of food, when the body breaks it down for storage, turns into a type of sugar.  This is why the diet of a diabetic person is [...]&lt;p&gt;This post via the &lt;a href="http://www.diabetescarenow.com"&gt;Diabetes Care&lt;/a&gt; site, where you can get information and resources about diabetes symptoms, gestational diabetes, and more.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/diabetes-menu-tips-and-information/"&gt;Diabetes Menu Tips and Information&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;



More Diabetes Care information:&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/diabetes-menu-sample-tips/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Diabetes Menu Sample Tips'&gt;Diabetes Menu Sample Tips&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Diabetes Menu To help learn the easiest way to...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/tips-and-tricks-to-free-diabetes-recipes/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Tips and Tricks to Free Diabetes Recipes'&gt;Tips and Tricks to Free Diabetes Recipes&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Free Diabetes Recipes If you have lately conducted an...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/gestational-diabetes-diet-tips-and-information/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Gestational Diabetes Diet Tips and Information'&gt;Gestational Diabetes Diet Tips and Information&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Gestational Diabetes Diet Gestational diabetes is just as serious...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/diabetes-care-tips/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Diabetes Care Tips'&gt;Diabetes Care Tips&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Diabetes Care Diabetes is a major disease even though...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/the-best-gestational-diabetes-recipes-tips/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: The Best Gestational Diabetes Recipes Tips'&gt;The Best Gestational Diabetes Recipes Tips&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Gestational Diabetes Recipes Eating right with gestational diabetes is...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/diabetes-care/Diabetes_Care-Diabetes_Menu_Tips_and_Information.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center>
<p style="text-align:center;"><object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/XGOebHvfQlU&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/XGOebHvfQlU&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></embed></object></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XGOebHvfQlU">Diabetes Menu</a></p>
<p></center>
<p>Diabetes is a disorder where the body doesn't produce enough insulin to cover the consumption of food a person intakes, causing the blood sugar levels to rise.  Plenty of food, when the body breaks it down for storage, turns into a type of sugar.  This is why the diet of a diabetic person is vital.  Someone who is diabetic desires to observe what they are eating to help control their blood sugar levels as much as possible, whatever if they're Type one or Type two. </p>
<p> This does not mean a person cannot eat what they want or that they must stick to a diet that is largely all vegetables or fruits.  As a diabetic, one desires to eat a range of different foods and in the right proportions to help maintain as healthy of a diet as practical, just like someone who is not diabetic.  Proteins are just as vital to a diabetic diet as veg, fruits, carbohydrates and the like. </p>
<p> Proteins help to maintain steady blood sugar levels.  Carbs, when the body breaks it down, turns into a sugar.  This is the reason why it is counseled for an individual who has hypoglycemia to eat a carbohydrate and a protein to help cause the blood sugar level to rise.  The sugar causes it to rise while the protein helps keep the blood sugar level there, instead of dropping again.  Now, you can see how the correct diet is vital for a diabetic. </p>
<p> Diabetic Menu<br /> The menu for a diabetic can be flexible.  It does not need to be'set'.  The diabetic menu should be low in sugar, of course, and contain masses of proteins and vitamins.  Do take under consideration that sugar can hide in different forms.  You may desire to discover how to read the nutritive label of all foods and if they do not have one, there are books which will aid you in learning the nutritional rules for that particular food.  Because something claims that it is sugar free, doesn't mean that it is.  If it is sugar free and still has carbohydrates listed on the label, then technically, it has sugar. </p>
<p> The best way to be told how to prepare a diabetic menu is to get a diabetic cookbook or to consult with a dietary specialist.  They can help to educate you what to look for, what to avoid and what you may have plenty of.  For example : meat ( non-breaded ), cheese and eggs are virtually carbohydrate free, so if you are searching for a snack, then these are perfect as they won't affect your blood sugar levels.  ( Eggs do have one gram of carbohydrates, so only eat less than four, otherwise, it will impact on your blood sugar levels. </p>
<p> don't forget the condiments<br /> Yes, condiments do affect blood sugar levels.  When deciding on your menu, take into consideration the condiments that you will be using.  Spices don't count ; although and so on should be used parsimoniously.  Also, flour causes blood sugar levels to rise, so anything that is breaded should be consumed sparingly. <br /> there's a lot to digest about diabetic diets and how to prepare a diabetic menu ; after you start doing it, it'll just become natural.  You'll automatically know that one piece of white bread is around 11-16 grams of carbs and then you will learn which brand to purchase ( the lower carbohydrate total ) so that you are able to consume more.</p>
<p>Come visit us here for your three free Diabetic Diet Ebooks: <a href="http://diabeticdietzone.com/">Diabetic Menu</a> http://diabeticdietzone.com.</p>
