      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center>
<p style="text-align:center;"><object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/fyKc2JqYu6M&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/fyKc2JqYu6M&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></embed></object></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fyKc2JqYu6M">Diabetes Videos</a></p>
<p></center>
<p> Diabetes is something that we hear a lot about these days.  Unfortunately, there is a rising number of young people being diagnoses as having diabetes.  It's a significant challenge that must not be ignored.  If you believe you will have diabetes, you want to search out a medical professional for help.  It's a lifetime disease that may cause a large amount of issues, including blindness.  Just look at all the diabetes videos online, and you will see many diabetics speaking out and caution others about the sickness. </p>
<p> unfortunately , a computed 1/3 of diabetics don't even know that they have the condition!  These people will often gain weight and experience difficulties brought on by the unduly extreme levels of glucose ( sugar ) in their blood, but will not even realizing what is happening to them!  And it's not something that just the aged get these days ; there is also Gestational and juvenile diabetes. </p>
<p> Gestational Diabetes<br /> if you are pregnant, or know someone who is, be sure to watch some Gestational diabetes videos to learn more info.  Roughly 4% of pregnant women in the US finish up with this type of diabetes.  It is essential that they get treated as soon as possible  or else they risk giving birth to a strangely large infant.  This isn't healthy for the mummy or the child.  Gestational diabetes can occur between the 24th and 28th week of pregnancy. </p>
<p> Type I &amp; II Diabetes<br /> Type II diabetes is the most common form, and accounts for ninety percent or so of all cases.  This is the type that is related to obesity and being overweight.  It is believed by gurus that family history plays a role.  Type I diabetes is related to insulin-dependence.  If you're diagnosed as having Type I, you can watch diabetes videos for tips on administering your medicine. </p>
<p> Dieting and Exercise<br /> in addition to taking medication under direction of your doctor, you must also decide to eat healthy foods and to exercise.  There are plenty of good foods out there that are healthy for diabetics to eat.  You want a well balanced diet that includes whole grains, protein, and plenty of water.  You can watch diabetes videos on ways to create a meal plan.  You may also surf for information, as there are plenty of sample meal plans for diabetics. </p>
<p> You also need to exercise some.  You can walk a few miles a number of times weekly, take up jogging, exercise to work out videos, hike, and so on.  Just make sure you do SOMETHING physically active each day or each other day.  Exercising, with dieting and taking medicine, will help control your blood sugar levels.  This will help you to lose weight and help in dealing with your diabetes. </p>
<p> Conclusion<br /> While there isn't any cure, you can still keep diabetes in hand.  You don't have to let it devastate your life.  There's help out there---you just need to go and get it.  Take a look at some diabetes videos online to get a better appreciation of the illness and how it can be handled.  Many of us are ready to share their experiences with others.  Health care executives also present useful recommendation and guidelines to diabetics thru net videos.</p>
<p>Come visit us here for your three free Diabetic Diet Ebooks: <a href="http://diabeticdietzone.com/">Diabetes Videos</a> http://diabeticdietzone.com.</p>
