More Diabetes Care information:&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/learn-about-type-1-diabetes-symptoms-associations/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Learn About Type 1 Diabetes Symptoms Associations'&gt;Learn About Type 1 Diabetes Symptoms Associations&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Type 1 Diabetes Symptoms Type 1 diabetes is often...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/gestational-diabetes-symptoms-tricks-information/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Gestational Diabetes Symptoms Tricks Information'&gt;Gestational Diabetes Symptoms Tricks Information&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Gestational Diabetes Symptoms Diabetes symptoms, if it is gestational...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/type-2-diabetes-symptoms-tricks-information/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Type 2 Diabetes Symptoms Tricks Information'&gt;Type 2 Diabetes Symptoms Tricks Information&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Type 2 Diabetes Symptoms Type two diabetes is actually...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/diabetes-mellitus-tricks-information/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Diabetes Mellitus Tricks Information'&gt;Diabetes Mellitus Tricks Information&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Diabetes Mellitus Diabetes mellitus is a monstrous illness.  It...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/diabetes-test-tips/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Diabetes Test Tips'&gt;Diabetes Test Tips&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Diabetes Test To find out if you're a diabetic...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/diabetes-care/Diabetes_Care-Diabetes_Symptoms_Information.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center>
<p style="text-align:center;"><object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/_dospatfboY&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/_dospatfboY&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></embed></object></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_dospatfboY">Diabetes Symptoms</a></p>
<p></center>
<p>Diabetes is affecting different folks in alternative ways.  This means that different folks may experience different symptoms and essentially there is a big variety of diabetes symptoms that are listed all across the different research which has been conducted and broadcast on this subject ; however there are some basic, common symptoms that can be a foundation for diabetes. </p>
<p> common indicators - There are some common manifestations that are found with folks who have diabetes.  These symptoms are typically more prevalent than any other symptoms that one could experience when it comes to diabetes. </p>
<p> 1..  Excessive, repeated thirst.  Continually being parched is certainly an indication of diabetes.  You can consistently drink and still feel as if though you haven't had anything.  If you notice yourself continually drinking something, you may need to inform your consultant. </p>
<p> 2.  Over the top urination.  Constant bathroom breaks during school or work or while just sitting at home is an indication of diabetes.  You should be in a position to leave your house and drive 10 miles without having to go to the bathroom ; unfortunately, this isn't necessarily true with the diabetic patient.  Another thing to have a look for is getting up in the middle of the night for a restroom break.  You should be able to go across the night without needing to get up and go to the bathroom.  If you find yourself waking up to use the restroom on a consistent basis inform your physician. </p>
<p> 3.  Weight reduction even with an increased appetite.  Your body is not getting any sugar through food intake ; however it starts to burn fat for energy.  So even though you eat, you can start to experience weight loss and possibly even quite a bit.  This can be extremely deadly as it usually means that you've got a high blood glucose level which can lead to a diabetic coma and ketoacidosis.  If you begin to shed kilos without basically trying, definitely inform your physician. </p>
<p> Time - agree with it or not is could take a span of several months before you can notice any of these symptoms.  This means that you might experience the exorbitant thirst for a bit, then perhaps the continual urination a month or so later.  If diabetes is not diagnosed and treated it can be really deadly.  When my girl was diagnosed, it did not'run' in our family and we failed to know the signs and symptoms.  We found her in a coma one morning with a blood glucose level of over 1482 mg/dL. </p>
<p> Ketoacidosis had set in and she was very lucky to wake up.  Once we found out about the signs and symptoms, I recalled back that she was actually showing these signs for months, but we did not know and we did not pick up on them.  And because she was a kid, the weight reduction was taken as she was just in an expansion spurt and slimming down.  In other words, don't instantly say that it is something, because you really never know unless you contact your physician.  Only they can test and confirm your suspicions.</p>
