      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center>
<p style="text-align:center;"><object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/EN4JqVDR2CY&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/EN4JqVDR2CY&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></embed></object></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EN4JqVDR2CY">Diabetic Recipes</a></p>
<p></center>
<p>Nutrition is one of the most important parts of controlling blood sugar levels and treating diabetes.  If you have diabetes and need to manage it the absolute best you can, then you want to commit to a healthy way of life, which encompasses a controlled diet, water, and exercise.  Not only should you take advantage of diabetes recipes to treat your diabetes, you need to do it as a way to improve your overall health.  There are lots of benefits to eating a healthy diet. <br /> Talk to your physician. </p>
<p> Talk to your physician about your desire to go on a diabetic diet.  A medicare supplier will help you invent a plan that will meet all your nutritional needs.  Following the right kind of diet for your own wants will help you in controlling both your blood sugar levels and weight.  You could also check to determine if there are any nutrition experts or registered dieticians in your area.  If this is so contact them immediately and ask for some good, delicious diabetes recipes. </p>
<p> Finding recipes on your own. <br /> You can always look online for some great diabetes recipes.  If you have already got a meal under consideration , there's definitely a recipe or two online that you're going to appreciate.  There are thousands of recipes for well-balanced meals, snacks, and deserts.  The cool thing is that you'll be able to find a variety of recipes so you do not get stuck eating the same meals repeatedly again! <br /> keep in mind that it is always best to eat 5 - 6 times a day, just so long as it is all healthy and well balanced.  It is OK to eat small snacks in between meals.  That way, you'll be less sure to over eat during meals! <br /> to offer you some ideas about the sorts of diabetes recipes you can find online, here are a few you may be curious about. <br /> Zingy Baked Chicken</p>
<p> Leave some skinless, boneless chicken and marinade in Italian dressing in your refrigerator overnight. <br /> Roll the chicken fillets in a mix of bread crumbs, parmesan cheese, and herbs. <br /> put them in a shallow pan and set your oven on bake for forty mins at 350.  Cook till the chicken is golden brown. <br /> Serve with fresh veggies! </p>
<p> Baked Tuna Macaroni and Cheese<br /> you will need :</p>
<p> 1/3 cup of fat free milk<br /> 10 cream of mushroom soup canned<br /> one tsp dried parsley<br /> 2 cup macaroni and pasta<br /> cup of drained and sliced pimentos<br /> 1/8 tsp of black pepper<br /> 18 tbsp of shredded, mild cheddar cheese<br /> 6 oz. of canned white tuna</p>
<p> heat your oven to 375 degrees F. <br /> Mix skim milk, mushroom soup, black pepper, and parsley flakes in a skillet. <br /> Add cheddar cheese into the mix and stir. <br /> Cook over medium heat and stir until the cheddar cheese softens. <br /> Stir in the tuna, macaroni, and pimiento. <br /> Spread the mixture in an 8' x 8' baking dish.  Make sure the dish is sprayed with cooking spray. <br /> Bake for approximately twenty-five mins. <br /> Take the dish out of the stove and let it set for one or two minutes before dividing into servings. <br /> But, what about dessert!? <br /> fortunately , there are tons of great diabetes recipes online for puddings.  You can enjoy cake, cookies, brownies, pie, &amp; more! <br /> Here is a great recipe for butterscotch and pumpkin pudding :<br /> one package of butterscotch putting ( make sure it is sugar free )<br /> 1 cup of pumpkin ( fresh )<br /> cup of low fat or skim milk<br /> 1 tea spoon of vanilla and cinnamon each<br /> tsp of nutmeg<br /> Cool whip</p>
<p> Now, mix all these together and make yourself some pudding!  Set them within individual containers and set them in the fridge.  You can then top them with cool whip if you want!</p>
