      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center>
<p style="text-align:center;"><object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/9QK0Lz82e6M&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/9QK0Lz82e6M&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></embed></object></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9QK0Lz82e6M">Diabetes Mellitus</a></p>
<p></center>
<p>Diabetes mellitus is a monstrous illness.  It can lead to heart disease, neuropathy, kidney failure, and even blindness.  If you think you may have diabetes, you need to get control of it as fast as possible.  If you're uncertain, you need to visit a surgeon for a checkup right now.  An approximate one out of 3 US people has the symptoms diabetes mellitus and does not even realize it.  You do not wish to be part of the 1/3 statistic.  Visit a doctor at this time if you have any reason to believe you could be diabetic. </p>
<p> Symptoms and indications of diabetes mellitus</p>
<p> these are some signs and symptoms that individuals with diabetes might have or experience. <br /> you do not exercise more than thirty mins or so a day ( cycling, walking, and so on.  )<br /> Some of the members of your family are or have been diabetic. <br /> You are constantly parched, and it appears as if you can never get sufficient water. <br /> if you're always feeling feeble and fatigued, no matter how much sleep you get. <br /> You are visiting the bathroom frequently---much more than what is common for you. <br /> You notice that your vision is beginning to become somewhat blurry at times. </p>
<p> These are some of the signs.  If you experience any of these, you may have diabetes mellitus.  Naturally, these signs can be due to other reasons, and not just diabetes, thus you must visit a doctor to discover for sure.  It is better to be safe than sorrowful, after all. </p>
<p> Fasting blood glucose test<br /> This is the preferred methodology of diagnosing diabetes mellitus.  You will be needed to fast for a minimum of eight hours.  A sample of your blood will be drawn and sent to the laboratory for research.  This may also be done in a physician's office employing a glucose meter. </p>
<p> The results can be as follows :<br /> The fasting plasma glucose levels, when ordinary, are less than one hundred mg per dl ( deciliter ). <br /> Fasting plasma glucose levels of 126 mg/dl or more on two or three tests on different days indicates diabetes mellitus. <br /> A blood glucose level of 200 mg/dl + indicates diabetes mellitus also.  This is particularly so if the test is random. </p>
<p> Do not worry or permit yourself to become stressed if you believe you or somebody you know may have diabetes.  Just know that you are not alone, as millions of others have this sickness also.  While there isn't any cure, it can be handled through medication, dieting, and exercise.  There are also some home treatments that are believed to help treat diabetes. </p>
<p> One of the smartest things you can do is change your diet.  It could be hard to do at first, but if you do so, you can lessen the indications of diabetes mellitus a great deal.  Just look online for a sample meal plan for diabetics.  As well as visiting a doctor and getting acceptable medication, you should also visit a diet consultant or nutrition consultant to help you formulate a healthy weight loss program.  There are plenty of good meals and desserts that diabetics can safely eat.  In reality, some will even help make you healthier!</p>
<p>Come visit us here for your three free Diabetic Diet Ebooks: <a href="http://diabeticdietzone.com/">Diabetes Mellitus</a> http://diabeticdietzone.com.</p>
