      <description>Diabetes Dessert Recipes

If you're a diabetic, you'll be glad to understand that you can eat desserts!  You can still enjoy the things that everybody else eats.  You do need to be choosier, but there are loads of selections available for you nevertheless.  Do not believe in the common myth that diabetics cannot consume sugar.  There [...]&lt;p&gt;This post via the &lt;a href="http://www.diabetescarenow.com"&gt;Diabetes Care&lt;/a&gt; site, where you can get information and resources about diabetes symptoms, gestational diabetes, and more.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/learning-diabetes-dessert-recipes/"&gt;Learning Diabetes Dessert Recipes&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;



More Diabetes Care information:&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/learning-gestational-diabetes-recipes/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Learning Gestational Diabetes Recipes'&gt;Learning Gestational Diabetes Recipes&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Gestational Diabetes Recipes Approximately five percent of all pregnant...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/diabetes-recipes-tips-and-information/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Diabetes Recipes Tips and Information'&gt;Diabetes Recipes Tips and Information&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Diabetic Recipes Nutrition is one of the most important...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/easy-diabetes-recipes-tricks-information/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Easy Diabetes Recipes Tricks Information'&gt;Easy Diabetes Recipes Tricks Information&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Easy Diabetes Recipes If you have diabetes, you do...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/find-pre-diabetes-recipes/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Find Pre Diabetes Recipes'&gt;Find Pre Diabetes Recipes&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Pre Diabetes Recipes The best pre diabetes recipes can...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/tips-and-tricks-to-free-diabetes-recipes/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Tips and Tricks to Free Diabetes Recipes'&gt;Tips and Tricks to Free Diabetes Recipes&lt;/a&gt; &lt;small&gt; Free Diabetes Recipes If you have lately conducted an...&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/diabetes-care/Diabetes_Care-Learning_Diabetes_Dessert_Recipes.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center>
<p style="text-align:center;"><object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/o8fqanz7Zpo&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/o8fqanz7Zpo&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></embed></object></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o8fqanz7Zpo">Diabetes Dessert Recipes</a></p>
<p></center>
<p>If you're a diabetic, you'll be glad to understand that you can eat desserts!  You can still enjoy the things that everybody else eats.  You do need to be choosier, but there are loads of selections available for you nevertheless. <br /> Do not believe in the common myth that diabetics cannot consume sugar.  There are lots of mouth watering puddings out there you can eat.  You can still lose weight if you help yourself to the occasional treat.  Just so long as your doctor tells you that it is fine to eat dessert, then you can do so on occasion!  The internet is filled with lots of diabetes pudding recipes for cookies, sundaes, pie, cake, and more. </p>
<p> Here are some diabetes pudding recipes that you will find useful. <br /> Warm Apple Cinnamon Cobbler<br /> 4 apples - chopped, cored, and peeled<br /> two little spoons of ground cinnamon<br /> 1 cup of water<br /> 2 tablespoons of cornstarch<br /> 1 cup of unprocessed wheat pastry flour<br /> of cup fructose<br /> fourteen cup of canola oil<br /> one tsp of baking powder<br /> one tbsp of honey<br /> cup of low fat buttermilk</p>
<p> preheat the cooker to 375 degrees F. <br /> mix the water, apples, cornstarch, fructose, and cinnamon in to a sauce pan over gentle heat. <br /> pour the apple mixture into a dish. <br /> combine the pastry flour with the baking powder to make biscuit dough. <br /> Add the canola oil and stir well. <br /> Next, add the buttermilk and honey, and stir with a fork till the mixture is clammy. <br /> decant the biscuit dough on the apples with tablespoos. <br /> cook for twenty mins or so until done. <br /> Serve warm and enjoy! </p>
<p> Strawberry Banana Sundae<br /> one package of sugar free strawberry gelatin<br /> six ice cubes<br /> one cup of boiling water<br /> four fresh strawberries<br /> four large spoons of whipped topping</p>
<p> Take a small bowl and allow the jelly to dissolve in boiling water. <br /> Let the bowl cool for 10 mins. <br /> Place the ice and jelly into the blender, cover, and process until ice is dissolved. <br /> Add bananas, and mix for another minute or two. <br /> tip into 4 dishes, and cool for thirty minutes or until set. <br /> Garnish each with a strawberry and big spoon of whipped topping! </p>
<p> Almond Biscotti</p>
<p> cup of sugar<br /> cup of thinly sliced almonds<br /> 4 egg whites---lightly beaten<br /> 2 teaspoons of almond extract<br /> small spoon of salt<br /> two cups of utility flour<br /> 2teaspoons of baking powder<br /> 2 tablespoons of margarine</p>
<p> -Preheat your stove to 375 degrees F.  Place the almonds into a baking pan, and then heat for 7 or eight mins.  Watch rigorously for the almonds to turn golden brown, and then set aside. </p>
<p> -Beat marg and sugar into medium sized bowl with blender.  When smooth, add whites of the eggs and almond extract.  Continue to mix, and then combine flour, salt, and baking powder into a large bowl.  Mix that as well, and then stir almonds and white of the egg mix into flour mixture.  Make sure it is well blended. </p>
<p> -With cooking spray, spray two 9' x 5' loaf pans.  Evenly divide the dough and spread it between pans.  Spread uniformly over the bottoms of the pans with wet fingertips. </p>
<p> -Bake fifteen minutes or so.  Insert a knife into the center to ensure that it is done. </p>
<p> -Turn loaves onto cutting board, and as quickly as they are cooled down, cut each into sixteen,' thick slices! </p>
<p> -Place slices onto baking sheets sprayed with cooking spray.  Heat for five more minutes ; turn slices over and bake five minutes on other side, or till golden brown. </p>
<p> -Serve and enjoy!</p>
