      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center>
<p style="text-align:center;"><object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/jb6sRduKWHk&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/jb6sRduKWHk&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></embed></object></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jb6sRduKWHk">Type 1 Diabetes Symptoms</a></p>
<p></center>
<p>Type 1 diabetes is often referred to as Diabetes Mellitus and Juvenile Onset Diabetes.  Type one diabetes is when the body has attacked the pancreas, which contains the cells that produce the hormone called insulin.  When the body does this, its natural capability to supply its own insulin is taken away ; although requiring the employment of insulin injections usually for the rest of their life. </p>
<p> Insulin injections will be necessary at every meal time and at bed time.  Most Type one diabetics take roughly 3-4 insulin injections every day.  Diabetes Mellitus is a particularly heavy condition and you will need to receive treatment as quickly as you most likely can if you feel as if though you may be a diabetic. <br /> Symptoms- Type one Diabetes Symptoms include :</p>
<p> 1.  Exorbitant thirst<br /> 2. Excessive urination.  Really concentrate on see whether or not you are waking up in the middle of the night to use the restroom.  This may definitely be a tell-tell <a href="http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-symptoms/sign-of-diabetes/" >sign of diabetes</a>. <br /> 3. Abdominal pain<br /> 4. Fatigue<br /> 5.  Weight loss.  As the body is unable to use the energy that is being consumed and the sugar is staying in the blood stream, your body will start to burn energy that it has stored in the form of fat.  This is the reason why you'll experience weight reduction even though you may still have a normal appetite or have not modified your diet. <br /> 6. Lack of menstruation<br /> 7.  Nausea<br /> 8.  Vomiting</p>
<p> Diabetes affects each patient in other ways.  If you look in the various publications that are available about diabetes there are actually many different symptoms.  Simply because one patient may experience one symptom doesn't mean the same symptom will be prevalent in another patient. </p>
<p> The above eight symptoms are just the common symptoms that are experienced by Type one diabetic patients.  These are the symptoms that are generally seen and can be associated with Type one diabetes more so than any other symptom. </p>
<p> remember that you could experience more than one of these symptoms and the symptoms could take a period of time to develop.  In other words, you might experience the increased thirst symptom and then a month later start experiencing the unwarranted pissing.  This means that you have basically been diabetic for a month without receiving hospital therapy and this can lead to a threatening situation.  So, to be safe, when you start experiencing the first indication of Type one diabetes you need to inform your physician as soon as possible in order that they can schedule a glucose tolerance test to accurately establish whether or not you are a diabetic or not. </p>
<p> Don't automatically assume that one of these symptoms is related to something else.  The truth is you may never know.  You must inform your consultant as soon as possible because if not treated, blood glucose levels will continue to rise which can lead to a diabetic coma, ketoacidosis and possibly even death.  Diabetes is a serious condition and may be regarded seriously and treated as fast as possible.</p>
<p>Come visit us here for your three free Diabetic Diet Ebooks: <a href="http://diabeticdietzone.com/">Type 1 Diabetes Symptoms</a> http://diabeticdietzone.com.</p>
