More Diabetes Care information:<ol><li><a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/learn-about-type-1-diabetes-symptoms-associations/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Learn About Type 1 Diabetes Symptoms Associations'>Learn About Type 1 Diabetes Symptoms Associations</a> <small> Type 1 Diabetes Symptoms Type 1 diabetes is often...</small></li><li><a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/gestational-diabetes-symptoms-tricks-information/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Gestational Diabetes Symptoms Tricks Information'>Gestational Diabetes Symptoms Tricks Information</a> <small> Gestational Diabetes Symptoms Diabetes symptoms, if it is gestational...</small></li><li><a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/diabetes-symptoms-information/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Diabetes Symptoms Information'>Diabetes Symptoms Information</a> <small> Diabetes Symptoms Diabetes is affecting different folks in alternative...</small></li><li><a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/most-noticeable-diabetes-symptoms/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Most Noticeable Diabetes Symptoms'>Most Noticeable Diabetes Symptoms</a> <small> Diabetes symptoms be able to avoid those at risk...</small></li><li><a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/type-1-diabetes/type-1-diabetes-insulin/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Type 1 Diabetes Insulin'>Type 1 Diabetes Insulin</a> <small> People with Type 1 diabetes will always have it....</small></li></ol>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center>
<p style="text-align:center;"><object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/wK0uz2F59b0&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/wK0uz2F59b0&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></embed></object></p>
<p style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wK0uz2F59b0">Type 2 Diabetes Symptoms</a></p>
<p></center>
<p>Type two diabetes is actually totally different than Type two diabetes.  With Type 2, your body still can actually produce its own insulin although it may not produce enough or the cells would possibly not be accepting it.  You could need the help of insulin injections or medication to keep your body on the right track.  Sometimes you can also help your body out by shedding pounds, watching your diet and exercising. </p>
<p> Symptoms - Type 2 diabetes symptoms are customarily not as prevalent as the indicators of Type two diabetes.  They are usually slow to happen and take time to develop before you will even see them.  Some of the Type two diabetes symptoms are :</p>
<p> one.  Increased thirst and frequent urination.  Excessive sugar in the blood stream causes liquids to be withdrawn from the tissues inside your body.  This can cause your thirst level to extend and of course if you are drinking more, you'll urinate more . <br /> 2.  Fatigue.  As the body is not able to consume the energy that is required through the use of sugar, you may feel beat. <br /> 3.  Weight loss.  Once more, the body is not able to use the sugar for energy ; therefore it will start to use alternative means of energy, such as fat which has been stored for later use.  So even though you are still eating and not trying to lose pounds, you can experience weight loss. <br /> 4.  Hunger.  The body can't move insulin into the cells and can't use the energy that you are consuming ; therefore your cells may start to feel deprived which in turn can cause intense hunger pains. <br /> five.  Blurred vision.  With high blood sugar levels, fluids may start to be pulled away from the lens of your eyes which in turn can cause vision problems. <br /> 6.  Cuts that are slow to fix.  This is characteristic of the diabetic patient.  Pay attention to cuts that are slowly healing.  If not sorted they can result in the area needing to be amputated. <br /> 7.  Areas of darkened skin. <br /> eight.  Frequent infections</p>
<p> a few of these symptoms coincide with the indicators of Type two diabetes ; hence some are way more prevalent with Type two diabetes than with Type two diabetes.  For instance, areas of darkened skin are far more associated with Type 2 diabetes as it is generally an indication of insulin resistance. </p>
<p> Take all signs and symptoms of diabetes seriously.  When you first notice that something won't be right, contact your consultant.  Diabetes wishes medical care and guidance.  If you continue to blank the fact that you could possibly have diabetes, you health can be significantly affected and diabetes that's not looked after can result in death. </p>
<p> If is crucial that you seek medical advice and/or attention as fast as possible when you have spotted a sign or symptom of diabetes.  The physician will send you to get a blood test that will help to ascertain the diagnosis.  It is actually as easy and as simple as that.</p>
