      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The amount of sugar in our body is for a time known as blood glucose level. When foods are eaten, the body will exceed it down into the simplest form, namely glucose. Glucose is the fuel for our body where it is the major source of energy for the cells. The cell take out glucose from the blood stream by using insulin. <a href="http://best-health-beauty.us/diabetes-type-1">Diabetes Type I</a> occurs when the body loses its aptitude to create insulin making the removal of glucose from the blood stream impossible. As a result the sugar content in the blood increases.</p>
<p> The symptoms for diabetes type 1 may well vary for every person, but these are the extra ordinary symptoms.</p>
<p> Often diabetic type 1 occurs without any signs or symptoms.</p>
<p> - Sugar content are higher than the ordinary blood sugar content<br /> - The urine is laced with sugar<br /> - Drinks unusual sum of water<br /> - Urinates recurrently<br /> - Lose weight even though regularly feels hungry<br /> - Eyesight becomes blurry<br /> - Feeling nauseous<br /> - Feels lethargic and weak<br /> - <a href="http://best-health-beauty.us/womens-fragrances">Mood</a> swings</p>
<p> While there are no heal for diabetes, treating it and controlling diabetes will further aggravate the trouble to other important <a href="http://best-health-beauty.us/healthy-breakfast">health</a> problems such as heart danger and stroke. To reduce other health risks, it is important that the blood sugar level are maintained to regular as close as possible.</p>
<p> The steps listed under are some of the steps that can be taken to control diabetes type 1:</p>
<p> - Never skip insulin as prescribe<br /> - Eat healthy by watching the total of carbohydrate you take and follow diabetic diet plan as strictly as possible.<br /> - Watch your blood sugar content without fail<br /> - Get physical exercise and do it regularly</p>
<p> Treating diabetes will help the body maintains as close to normal its blood sugar substance. Diabetes type 1 are all-time sickness where there are no treat, as such the treatments is also lifelong. To stay healthy, diabetics must watch lifelong treatments through correct eating and exercising all through their lives.</p>
