      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Diet is one of the most vital components of a diabetes care and maintenance regimen. With the diabetic food exchange list is an terrific way to ensure a healthy meal all time. It also helps expand your choices when preparing or choosing a menu.</p>
<p>What is the Diabetic Food Exchange List?</p>
<p>The diabetic food exchange list is a system that makes up the structure of your personal diabetes meal plan. It is quite successful especially if you're looking for multiplicity in your diet without sacrificing the required elements that are required for your condition. This way, you can take a look at several types of foods available and then desire which ones to usage for a particular meal with no worrying you might be with the wrong diversity of food or food combination.</p>
<p>How Does It Work?</p>
<p>In the <a href="http://best-health-beauty.us/diabetes-cure">diabetic food</a> exchange list, foods are grouped into any important types - fruits, dairy and dairy goods, starches, meat and meat substitutes, sugars, et cetera. The exchange list will speak you how much of each food in every group you be able to eat as maintaining your daily recommended calories because calorie information is included with each food portion.</p>
<p>Each food on the exchange list is called an "exchange" and the system will guide you in determining which foods equal 1 exchange. It's easy to substitute one food for the other since the exchange list will indicate which foods have the same nutrients, carbohydrate and calorie content. If you swap a certain food with another, you acquire the same nutrients provided you follow the suggested portion control.</p>
<p>The diabetic food exchange list will help you measure food, regardless of which group it belongs to. This means you won't need the assistance of a nutritionist or dietitian every step along the way. Long-term handling of the exchange list will train you into knowing how to make great estimates of the ideal serving size of any food that can be available to you at several <a href="http://best-health-beauty.us/diabetes-causes">given moment</a>. Whichever you pick, you will get the same nutrients. Here's an example:</p>
<p>Vegetables</p>
<p>Almost all vegetables may possibly be included inside the diabetic food exchange list. One exchange is about half a cup of cooked or raw vegetables which contains carbohydrates and protein. When used using salad dressing, however, add 1 fat exchange.</p>
<p>Carbohydrates</p>
<p>Carbohydrates are an worthy component of a few diabetic diet since they are your body's primary source of energy. Approximately half of your daily calorie intake must come from this food group. Any of these foods may possibly be exchanged or <a href="http://best-health-beauty.us/diabetes-signs">swapped</a>, depending on your needs or preference:</p>
<p>1/2 hot dog or hamburger bun or 1 slice of bread<br />
1/3 cup of cooked pasta or a single 5-inch pancake.<br />
3/4 cup cereals (unsweetened) or ½ cup cooked oatmeal or grits<br />
1 tortilla or 6 small saltine crackers or 15 pcs. of fat free corn chips<br />
1/4 bagel or 1/2 pita bread</p>
<p>Fruits</p>
<p>Fruits be able to be an groovy source of fiber, water and expected sugar. The fruits listed below contain about 60 calories every with nearly zero fat.</p>
<p>1/4 cup water melon or 1/3 small cantaloupe or 1/2 cup berries<br />
1/2 cup orange/grapefruit juice or 1/2 cup of pineapple or apple juice or 1/3 cup grape juice<br />
1/2 banana or 1 small apple</p>
<p>Meats</p>
<p>Meats are an principal source of protein. Desire only lean meats and skinless portions for poultry. High-fat meats can improve your cholesterol level.</p>
<p>1 oz. tuna or 1 egg or 2 egg whites<br />
1 oz. ground beef or 1 oz. of low fat cheese or cottage cheese<br />
1 oz. of fish or 1 oz. of dark meat poultry (skinless)<br />
1 oz. lean pork or 1 oz. lean beef</p>
<p>Milk and Milk Goods</p>
<p>2/3 cup of fat free yogurt or 3/4 cup of yogurt sourced from 2% milk<br />
1 cup nonfat or skim milk or 1 cup 1% milk (2% milk will also do)</p>
<p>Sweets</p>
<p>The foods listed beneath are a terrific source of equally carbohydrates and fats but they be able to also be magnificent for your dessert inside case you have the craving.</p>
<p>1/3 cup low fat frozen yogurt or 1/2 cup ice cream<br />
1 2-inch square brownie or 2 small cookies or 1 granola bar</p>
<p>Extra Details On The Diabetic Food Exchange List</p>
<p>There are listings of food exchange lists available on sites such because diabetes.org for free but if you want a more comprehensive exchange list, you can also opt to purchase them. Only log on to the sites and arrange your own diabetic food exchange list online.</p>
