      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>We all know that too lots of people suffer from diabetes, which can be a killer illness, but a lot of of us do not know the answer to that elementary question.</p>
<p>What is diabetes?</p>
<p>Diabetes mellitus is, to put it very plainly, characterized by high levels of blood sugar. So what is diabetes <a href="http://best-health-beauty.us/acne-cause">caused</a> by? There are three types of diabetes: multiplicity 1, kind 2 and gestational diabetes. At present that we have answered, very usually, the question 'What is diabetes,' allow us go on to the first variety of diabetes.</p>
<p>Type 1 diabetes</p>
<p>Insulin, which our body needs to control the levels of sugar inside our blood, is created by the beta cells inside the pancreas, or, more specifically, inside the Islets of Langerhans, which is a part of the pancreas. Inside Kind 1 diabetes, these cells die as the autoimmune system attacks it. This is the variety of diabetes that you see in children, though it is seen inside adults, because healthy. <a href="http://best-health-beauty.us/dental-health-insurance">Careful</a> monitoring of the blood sugar levels and replacement of insulin is the treatment for type 1 diabetes. Even as the therapy cannot be stopped - it simply controls and regulates, it does not treatment - patients using kind 1 diabetes can live a usual and long life since long because they take the necessary precautions.</p>
<p>Type 2 diabetes</p>
<p>The next thing that stems from the question 'What is diabetes' is; what Selection 2 diabetes is. This combines resistance to insulin to lack of secretion of insulin, which is harder to handle than Type 1 diabetes. For this, first, the resistance be required to be decreased or eliminated, which can be done through proper diet and apply, and then the same treatment since for Variety 1 diabetes can be administered.</p>
<p>Gestational diabetes</p>
<p>Gestational <a href="http://best-health-beauty.us/what-is-diabetes">diabetes</a> is fairly ordinary and is the sort of diabetes that affects women during pregnancy.</p>
