      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><iframe src="http://rcm.amazon.com/e/cm?t=diabetescare-20&#038;o=1&#038;p=8&#038;l=as1&#038;asins=1580402879&#038;md=10FE9736YVPPT7A0FBG2&#038;fc1=5F5F5F&#038;IS2=1&#038;lt1=_blank&#038;m=amazon&#038;lc1=2266AA&#038;bc1=000000&#038;bg1=FFFFFF&#038;f=ifr" style="width:120px;height:240px;" scrolling="no" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" frameborder="0" rel="nofollow"></iframe></p>
<p>Dieting for weight loss can be difficult under the best of circumstances.  For those who are diabetic, weight loss diet planning is even more challenging.</p>
<p>Fortunately, the American Diabetes Association has put together a book that is meant to help diabetics understand the proper ways to diet.  The book, called "<a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1580402879?ie=UTF8&#038;tag=diabetescare-20&#038;linkCode=as2&#038;camp=1789&#038;creative=390957&#038;creativeASIN=1580402879" rel="nofollow">16 Myths of a Diabetic Diet</a>,"  will help you sort out fact from fiction when it comes to dieting and diabetes.</p>
<p>The contents of this book is to teach readers about the best diabetic meal plans, and to debunk common myths regarding diabetes and meal planning.  The fact that this book was published by the American Diabetes Association means it is a source that you can trust.  Readers of this book have rated it very highly.  <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1580402879?ie=UTF8&#038;tag=diabetescare-20&#038;linkCode=as2&#038;camp=1789&#038;creative=390957&#038;creativeASIN=1580402879" rel="nofollow">Go check out for yourself what readers of this book have to say about it, and see if it is right for you.</a></p>
