More Diabetes Care information:<ol><li><a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/gestational-diabetes/diet-for-gestational-diabetes/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Diet For Gestational Diabetes'>Diet For Gestational Diabetes</a> <small> Being pregnant can be hard enough.  The morning sickness,...</small></li><li><a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/gestational-diabetes-symptoms-tricks-information/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Gestational Diabetes Symptoms Tricks Information'>Gestational Diabetes Symptoms Tricks Information</a> <small> Gestational Diabetes Symptoms Diabetes symptoms, if it is gestational...</small></li><li><a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/gestational-diabetes/diabetes-of-pregnancy/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Diabetes of Pregnancy'>Diabetes of Pregnancy</a> <small> When a pregnant woman's blood glucose levels become too...</small></li><li><a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/type-1-diabetes/type-1-diabetes-treatments/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Type 1 Diabetes Treatments'>Type 1 Diabetes Treatments</a> <small> At this time, there is no cure for type...</small></li><li><a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/gestational-diabetes-diet-tips-and-information/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Gestational Diabetes Diet Tips and Information'>Gestational Diabetes Diet Tips and Information</a> <small> Gestational Diabetes Diet Gestational diabetes is just as serious...</small></li></ol>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="zemanta-img" style="margin: 1em; display: block;">
<div class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 210px"><a href="http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/Image:Expecting_mother.jpg"><img class=" " title="1 Diabetes Pregnancy" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/30/Expecting_mother.jpg/200px-Expecting_mother.jpg" alt="A picture of my wife" width="200" height="289" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Image via Wikipedia</p></div>
</div>
<p>If you are a pregnant woman with type 1 diabetes, pregnancy can be a time of concern.  There is good reason to be concerned, as your body will need an increased amount of insulin.  The last three months of your pregnancy will need the greatest increase.</p>
<p>The reason for the increased need of insulin is due to the placenta.  The placenta makes hormones that help your baby grow.  Unfortunately for you, these same hormones also tend to block the action of your insulin.  The result is that you need more insulin.</p>
<p>The good news is that your doctor will be able to help you maintain the proper insulin levels in your body.  You may even want to meet with a dietician to create meal plans that will be nutritionally balanced for you and your baby.</p>
