More Diabetes Care information:<ol><li><a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/top-diabetes-type-1-tips/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Top Diabetes Type 1 Tips!'>Top Diabetes Type 1 Tips!</a> <small> The amount of sugar in our body is for...</small></li><li><a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/top-diabetes-care-news-on-march-26-2009/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Top Diabetes Care News on March 26, 2009'>Top Diabetes Care News on March 26, 2009</a> <small> Q&amp;A: will tomatoes will cause an increase in blood...</small></li><li><a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/type-1-diabetes/type-1-diabetes-insulin/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Type 1 Diabetes Insulin'>Type 1 Diabetes Insulin</a> <small> People with Type 1 diabetes will always have it....</small></li><li><a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/know-about-type-2-diabetes-diet/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Know About Type 2 Diabetes Diet'>Know About Type 2 Diabetes Diet</a> <small> If you have diabetes then you are going to...</small></li><li><a href='http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-care/how-to-live-healthy-and-properly-manage-diabetes/' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: How to Live Healthy and Properly Manage Diabetes'>How to Live Healthy and Properly Manage Diabetes</a> <small> Today, diabetes now affects around 16 million Americans and...</small></li></ol>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="Chocolate Cupcake" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/45419782@N00/3305923341/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0px initial initial;" title="Type 1 Diabetes Treatments" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3497/3305923341_501070c790_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Chocolate Cupcake" width="178" height="240" /></a>At this time, there is no cure for type 1 diabetes, though research is being conducted to, hopefully, change that someday.  People with type 1 diabetes will have to deal with this disease for their entire lives.</p>
<p>Fortunately, type 1 diabetes treatments will help people manage their diabetes.  This is important to help prevent health problems, such as diabetes-related strokes or heart attacks.</p>
<p>As with all types of diabetes, the most important treatment is to control blood sugar levels.  One of the best things diabetics can do is carefully maintain proper diets.</p>
<p>Insulin shots are needed to help maintain proper blood sugar levels, though some people are able to control their levels by eating properly and exercising regularly.  It is possible to maintain health this way, but it takes extreme dedication.</p>
<p>The good news is that type 1 diabetes is a manageable diseases.  Many people with this type of diabetes have lived long, happy lives once they learned how to watch and maintain their blood sugar levels.</p>
