      <description><![CDATA[When a pregnant woman's blood glucose levels become too high, she will develop diabetes of pregnancy, commonly known as gestational diabetes.  This can be scary, but for most moms, the diabetes disappears after giving birth.
One of the problems of gestational diabetes is that the developing baby becomes too large, causing a difficult delivery.  It is [...]<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.diabetescarenow.com">Diabetes Care</a> site, where you can get information and resources about diabetes symptoms, gestational diabetes, and more.<br/><br/><a href="http://www.diabetescarenow.com/gestational-diabetes/diabetes-of-pregnancy/">Diabetes of Pregnancy</a></p>



