      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="Herb-Roasted Striped Bass with Asparagus and Cherry Tomatoes" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/12832970@N00/3381620930/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0px initial initial;" title="Recipes for diabetics" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3617/3381620930_3eca3fc3cf_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Herb-Roasted Striped Bass with Asparagus and Cherry Tomatoes" width="240" height="160" /></a>Eating right can be challenging for the best of us, but it is more than challenging for those with diabetes.  It is crucial.  The good news is that there are a lot of <a href="http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-diet/recipes-for-diabetics/" >recipes for diabetics</a> available.</p>
<p>You can visit your local library or bookstore to find recipes for all types of foods that are safe for those with diabetes to eat.  </p>
<p>Or, you can search the Internet for ebooks.  Ebooks are convenient as they tend to cost less than physical books and are easily downloaded to your computer.</p>
<p>Some sources that offer ebooks with recipes include:</p>
