      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="Jesica_12" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/29822531@N05/3248813755/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0px initial initial;" title="Diet for gestational diabetes" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3524/3248813755_ed4f119590_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Jesica_12" width="240" height="160" /></a>Being pregnant can be hard enough.  The morning sickness, the growing belly, being kicked from the inside.  Add gestational diabetes to this mix and things can get very stressful for the expecting mother.</p>
<p>Fortunately, it is possible to <a href="http://www.diabetescarenow.com/gestational-diabetes/diet-for-gestational-diabetes/" >diet for gestational diabetes</a> and control the diabetes.  Even better news, gestational diabetes disappears after the baby has been born</p>
<p>The best thing for a woman with gestational diabetes to do is contact a registered dietician who can help her come up with the best diet plan.  The dietician will help the mother with meal planning that will help her meet the weight gains and nutritional value of a normal pregnancy.  </p>
<p>Additionally, proper eating will help control the mother's blood sugar levels, which will keep both her and her baby healthy during the pregnancy.</p>
