      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="color: #0000ee; text-decoration: underline;"><a title="Blood Sugar Monitor" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/63603238@N00/379265729/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0px initial initial;" title="Insulin dependent diabetes mellitus" src="http://farm1.static.flickr.com/174/379265729_8c65b2ec63_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Blood Sugar Monitor" width="240" height="180" /></a></span></p>
<p><a href="http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-mellitus/insulin-dependent-diabetes-mellitus/" >Insulin dependent diabetes mellitus</a> (IDDM) is the term doctors use to describe diabetes mellitus, a type of diabetes that requires insulin therapy.  It is a severe form of diabetes that requires insulin.</p>
<p>The insulin is taken to avoid ketoacidosis, which is a life-threatening complication of diabetes mellitus.</p>
<p>People often confuse the term IDDM with juvenile diabetes mellitus and type 1 diabetes mellitus.  They are not, however, the same thing.</p>
<p>IDDM most often occurs in teenagers and young adults (typically under age 30).  However, it can also affect babies and children.</p>
