      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="Needle" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/93587218@N00/485746241/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0px initial initial;" title="Sign of Diabetes" src="http://farm1.static.flickr.com/228/485746241_57937bb23a_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Needle" width="240" height="103" /></a>Perhaps you are wondering if you have diabetes.  Have you had excessive thirst?  Experiencing unexplained weight loss?  It is possible that each of these symptoms is a <a href="http://www.diabetescarenow.com/diabetes-symptoms/sign-of-diabetes/" >sign of diabetes</a>.</p>
<p>If you suspect that you may be developing diabetes, then it is important that you see your doctor right away.  The sooner you have your diabetes officially diagnosed, the sooner you can begin treatment and start to feel better.</p>
<p>It is also important to rule out other medical issues that may be causing your symptoms.  If your weight loss or excessive thirst is not from diabetes then you will want to find out the cause and start dealing with it.</p>
